Drop the docs subdir from the build.

gdm's docs/meson.build calls gnome.yelp(), which unconditionally requires the
itstool program with no meson option to disable it. The yelp help pages are
irrelevant to our headless/QEMU target, so we remove the subdir rather than
pull in itstool. The Gdm-1.0 typelib and the daemon/greeter are unaffected.

--- a/meson.build
+++ b/meson.build
@@ -266,7 +266,6 @@
 if libcheck_dep.found()
   subdir('tests')
 endif
-subdir('docs')
 
 gnome.post_install(
   glib_compile_schemas: true,
